                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290409-270-victim2479 t18290409-270-viclabel1524"></join>, and drive hay and straw to town; I lost these two bit-halters and a crupper from my stable in my yard- I left them there on the night of the 9th of April, and missed them the next morning; the door had not been locked.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290409-270-person2481">
                  SAMUEL 
                  JOHNSON
               <interp inst="t18290409-270-person2481" type="surname" value="JOHNSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290409-270-person2481" type="given" value="SAMUEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290409-270-person2481" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a saddler, and live in Turnmill street. The prisoner came and offered two bit-halters for sale, for 4s.; I gave him no answer, and he went away - I informed the constable, who took him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290409-270-person2482">
                  JOHN 
                  ROBINSON
               <interp inst="t18290409-270-person2482" type="surname" value="ROBINSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290409-270-person2482" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290409-270-person2482" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the constable. Johnson told me, and I took the prisoner - he said he had brought up two horses to the Ram inn, in Smithfield, and was going to take them home to Hertfordshire; I said if he would go there I should be satisfied, but he would not; I was forced to call in another officer - we found this crupper on him.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I found the harness near Chigwell.</p>
